<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC4335E0841FC09FD71" box="[827,935,633,654]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">Remarks:</emphasis>
According to the principle of priority of the ICZN, this distinct genetic lineage should be named 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C4D4AFFEEFFC4335E088EFC2CFD34" authorityName="S. S." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[827,898,694,715]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Laudakia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="212" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stellio">
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC4335E088EFC2CFD34" box="[827,898,694,715]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">stellio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because that is the oldest available name. It includes already described morphological subspecies and other cryptic lineages of Clade 2, revealed by this study: the nominal 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC43478092BFB39FCD8" box="[1053,1175,786,808]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">
L. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C4D4AFFEEFFC4345E092BFB39FCD8" authorityName="S. S." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1083,1175,786,808]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Laudakia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="215" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stellio">s. stellio</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and its sister 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC4355A092AFA0DFCD8" box="[1343,1443,786,807]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">
<collectingCountry id="F35B7659FFEEFFC4355A092AFA0DFCD8" box="[1343,1443,786,807]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
subclade, 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC433CD090AFBB4FCB9" box="[936,1050,817,839]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">L. s. daani</emphasis>
and its sister 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC434D2090AFA0DFCB8" box="[1207,1443,817,839]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">W Taurus–Symi–Kaş</emphasis>
subclades, as well as the 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC4342B0968FB01FC9A" box="[1102,1199,848,869]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">
<collectingCountry id="F35B7659FFEEFFC4342B0968FB01FC9A" box="[1102,1199,848,869]" name="Lebanon" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC434800968FA84FC9A" box="[1253,1322,848,869]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">
<collectingCountry id="F35B7659FFEEFFC434800968FA84FC9A" box="[1253,1322,848,869]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">Hatay</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
subclades. The subspecific status of 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC434380957FB78FC7C" box="[1117,1238,878,900]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">
L. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C4D4AFFEEFFC4341E0957FB78FC7C" authorityName="S. S." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1147,1238,878,900]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Laudakia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="215" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stellio">s. stellio</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC435750957FA26FC7C" box="[1296,1416,878,900]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">L. s. daani</emphasis>
is retained, while the elevation of the 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC434A309B5FA89FC5D" box="[1222,1319,909,930]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">
<collectingCountry id="F35B7659FFEEFFC434A309B5FA89FC5D" box="[1222,1319,909,930]" name="Lebanon" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC4353809B6FA0CFC5C" box="[1373,1442,910,931]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">
<collectingCountry id="F35B7659FFEEFFC4353809B6FA0CFC5C" box="[1373,1442,910,931]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">Hatay</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
lineages to the subspecies level is under preparation.
</paragraph>
